Week 5 – Data Modeling
Objective
Build structured data model using Power BI.
We learned how to structure data properly for analysis using data modeling techniques in Power BI. We understood the concept of Fact Table and Dimension Tables, 
where the fact table contains transactional and measurable data like resolution time and CSAT score, and dimension tables contain descriptive attributes like region, channel, and priority.
We implemented a star schema, where the fact table is placed at the center and connected to multiple dimension tables. We also learned about relationships between tables, 
including one-to-many and many-to-one relationships, and the concept of cardinality. 
This helped in building a structured and optimized data model for better analysis.

